# Present before writing (meta-artifacts)

When creating or editing **generated meta-artifacts** — new rules, new commands, or new design-log sections beyond the standard template — do **not** write files immediately.

1. **Present the full draft** in your response (e.g. the complete rule text, command text, or design-log section).
2. **Wait for explicit user approval** (e.g. "yes", "looks good", "write it").
3. **Only then** create or overwrite the file(s).

This applies when the user asks to add or change rules, commands, or design-log section types. It does not apply to normal implementation work guided by existing design logs and commands.

Where relevant, workflow commands and design-log methodology should remind the model of this when the task involves creating a new rule or appending a new kind of content to a log.
